\ demo-rewrite.6th ‚Äî Formal graph rewriting: transitive-closure rule
\                    produces complete reachability as fixed point.
\
\ Claim demonstrated:
\   A single declarative substrate rule
\        for every 2-edge path x‚Üíy‚Üíz, ensure edge x‚Üíz
\   iterated to fixed point computes the transitive closure of a
\   directed graph.  Reachability is not assumed ‚Äî it emerges from
\   repeated application of a local rewrite over the edge set.
\
\   Uses EACH-2PATH: iterates over all 2-paths in snapshot, so rule
\   is order-independent (atomic step semantics).

: 2dup over over ;
: nip swap drop ;
: not 0 = ;

: zero MARK ;

\ TC rule: given 2-path (a,b,c), ensure a‚Üíc.
: tc-rule                                  \ ( a b c -- )
  nip                                      \ ( a c )   drop middle b
  2dup EDGE? if
    2drop                                  \ already there
  else
    EDGE+                                  \ add a‚Üíc
  then ;

\ ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ DEMO 1: chain a‚Üíb‚Üíc‚Üíd ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
zero "a" store
zero "b" store
zero "c" store
zero "d" store
"a" load "b" load EDGE+
"b" load "c" load EDGE+
"c" load "d" load EDGE+

NODES 4 = ASSERT
EDGES 3 = ASSERT

STEP
' tc-rule EACH-2PATH
\ 2-paths: a‚Üíb‚Üíc, b‚Üíc‚Üíd.  Add a‚Üíc, b‚Üíd.  Total 5.
EDGES 5 = ASSERT
"a" load "c" load EDGE? ASSERT
"b" load "d" load EDGE? ASSERT

STEP
' tc-rule EACH-2PATH
\ 2-paths now include a‚Üíb‚Üíd, a‚Üíc‚Üíd, b‚Üíc‚Üíd (existing).  Add a‚Üíd.
EDGES 6 = ASSERT
"a" load "d" load EDGE? ASSERT

STEP
' tc-rule EACH-2PATH
\ fixed point: no new edges possible
EDGES 6 = ASSERT

"a" load OUT 3 = ASSERT
"b" load OUT 2 = ASSERT
"c" load OUT 1 = ASSERT
"d" load OUT 0 = ASSERT

\ ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ DEMO 2: 3-cycle x‚Üíy‚Üíz‚Üíx ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
RESET
zero "x" store
zero "y" store
zero "z" store
"x" load "y" load EDGE+
"y" load "z" load EDGE+
"z" load "x" load EDGE+
NODES 3 = ASSERT
EDGES 3 = ASSERT

STEP
' tc-rule EACH-2PATH
\ 2-paths (all from snapshot): x‚Üíy‚Üíz, y‚Üíz‚Üíx, z‚Üíx‚Üíy.
\ Add: x‚Üíz, y‚Üíx, z‚Üíy.  Total 6.
EDGES 6 = ASSERT
"x" load "z" load EDGE? ASSERT
"y" load "x" load EDGE? ASSERT
"z" load "y" load EDGE? ASSERT

STEP
' tc-rule EACH-2PATH
\ Now 2-paths include x‚Üíy‚Üíx, x‚Üíz‚Üíx, etc ‚Üí self-loops emerge.
\ All 3 self-loops added.  Total 9 = K3 with self-loops.
EDGES 9 = ASSERT
"x" load "x" load EDGE? ASSERT
"y" load "y" load EDGE? ASSERT
"z" load "z" load EDGE? ASSERT

STEP
' tc-rule EACH-2PATH
\ fixed point
EDGES 9 = ASSERT

REPORT
